'''徐庆培'''（{{lang-en|Suh Kyung-bae}}, {{bd|1963年|1月14日|}}）是一位韩国企业家。

==生平==
1963年出生于[[韩国|韩国]]，毕业于[[延世大学|延世大学]]和[[康奈尔大学|康奈尔大学]][[S·C·约翰逊管理研究院|S·C·约翰逊管理研究院]]。<ref name="Forbes profile"/>1987年加入家族公司[[爱茉莉太平洋|爱茉莉太平洋]]负责业务拓展。2013年担任集团董事长。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/gracechung/2015/08/19/how-south-koreas-amorepacific-became-one-of-the-worlds-most-innovative-companies/|title=How South Korea's AmorePacific Became One Of The World's Most Innovative Companies|last=Chung|first=Grace|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-03-02|archive-date=2021-12-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211222211803/https://www.forbes.com/sites/gracechung/2015/08/19/how-south-koreas-amorepacific-became-one-of-the-worlds-most-innovative-companies/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==荣誉==
*2006年获得[[法國榮譽軍團勳章|法國榮譽軍團軍官勳章]]
*2014年《[[福布斯|福布斯]]》韩国富豪榜第五名
*2015年被《[[福布斯|福布斯]]》亚洲评为最佳企业家
*2017年被《[[哈佛商业评论|哈佛商业评论]]》和[[欧洲工商管理学院|欧洲工商管理学院]]商学院评为全球第二十位，亚洲第二位最佳表现企业家<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/chairman-and-ceo-of-amorepacific-group-suh-kyung-bae-ranks-20-on-harvard-business-reviews-best-performing-ceos-list-300544686.html|title=Chairman and CEO of Amorepacific Group Suh Kyung-bae Ranks #20 on Harvard Business Review's Best-Performing CEOs List|last=Amorepacific|website=www.prnewswire.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-02|archive-date=2020-09-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200920145730/https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/chairman-and-ceo-of-amorepacific-group-suh-kyung-bae-ranks-20-on-harvard-business-reviews-best-performing-ceos-list-300544686.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==家庭==
已婚有两个孩子，生活在[[首尔|首尔]]。

==慈善 ==
2016年成立徐庆培科学基金会，<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.suhf.org/main/index.do|title=서경배과학재단|website=www.suhf.org|access-date=2020-03-02|archive-date=2021-05-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210517013703/https://www.suhf.org/main/index.do|dead-url=no}}</ref>2017年向14位科学家颁发15亿至25亿韩元的奖金。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/gracechung/2019/12/02/asias-2019-heroes-of-philanthropy-catalysts-for-change/|title=Asia’s 2019 Heroes Of Philanthropy: Catalysts For Change|last=Chung|first=Grace|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-03-02|archive-date=2019-12-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203085936/https://www.forbes.com/sites/gracechung/2019/12/02/asias-2019-heroes-of-philanthropy-catalysts-for-change/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

